Crude Oily🛢️ WTI past 04Ds 30mins📈 rose to $83.38 per barrel on Friday holding close to a nine-month high of nearly $85as investors assess the global economy  interest rates  and IEA and OPEC outlooks. The IEA signaled potential declines in worldwide oil stockpiles throughout 2023  potentially pushing prices even higher. Nonetheless  the agency foresees a deceleration in demand growth during 2024 to about 1 million barrels per day (bpd)  down by 150 000 bpd from their earlier prediction. OPEC indicated an expectation for global oil demand to grow by 2.25 million bpd in 2024  slightly less than the projected 2.44 million bpd increase for the current year.
